         <listEvent>
            <event type="researchStep">
               <head type="stepTitle" xml:lang="en">Describe the project</head>
               <desc type="definition" xml:lang="en">
                  <list>
                     <item>Framework, analytical context (motivation - aim of the analytical campaign);
                Short presentation of the main objectives of the analysis of the
                artworks/monument</item>
                     <item>Preliminary analysis: Information about any preliminary visual examination and
                analysis of the artwork using other techniques such as photography, multispectral
                imaging, XRF, LIBS etc. The prelimenary analysis provides information on the
                condition and the characteristics of the artwork useful for an effective planning
                and appropriate selection of measurement points for Raman analysis.<list>
                           <item>Possible source of error: wrong selection of measurement position, relating
                    to previous measurements as LIBS (if ignored or not well-documented)</item>
                        </list>
                     </item>
                     <item>Known conservation history / archives / oral communication: Research in digital
                resources, archives and even oral communication with experts concerning information
                of past analytical data or conservation interventions<list>
                           <item>Possible source of error: possible interference of (aged) conservation
                    materials</item>
                        </list>
                     </item>
                  </list>
               </desc>
